  "texts": [
    "In the results of the specificity assessments conducted for ICD-10-CM coding, evaluations performed by Llama-3.1-70B and Qwen-2-72B reveal a significant preference for codes generated by LLMs over those assigned by humans (Figure 4c, 4d).",
    "These findings were consistent across several models, demonstrating the superior performance of LLMs in terms of specificity (p<0.001 for all models).",
    "When evaluated by Llama-3.1-70B, GPT-4 was notably recognized for its precision, receiving the highest preference with 288 instances where its specificity was favored, compared to 75 where human coders were preferred.",
    "Both Qwen-2-7B and Llama-3.1-70B itself also showed strong results, with Llama-3.1 being preferred in 273 cases against 103 for human coders.",
    "This pattern underscores the robustness of LLMs in ensuring detailed and precise coding."
  ],
